# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Project Overview

Fleet Control System ("Sistema Controle de Frota") — a single-page application for managing vehicles and their expenses (fuel, maintenance, inspections, etc.). The entire UI is in Brazilian Portuguese.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** Vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript (no framework, no build system, no package manager)
- **Backend/DB:** Firebase Firestore (real-time NoSQL) + Firebase Cloud Storage (file uploads)
- **Hosting:** Firebase Hosting (project ID: `controle-frota-mave`)
- **Fallback:** LocalStorage when Firebase is unavailable

## Deployment

```bash
firebase deploy
```

There is no build step, test runner, or linter configured. The app is a single HTML file served statically.

## Architecture

### Single-file SPA

All code lives in `public/index.html`: CSS styles, HTML structure, and JavaScript in one file. There is no module system or bundler.

### Page Navigation

Five pages managed via CSS class toggling (`.page.active`): Dashboard, Vehicles, Expenses, Reports, Analytics. Navigation is handled by `showPage()` which toggles visibility.

### Data Layer — Dual Storage Strategy

The app detects whether Firebase credentials are configured at startup:
- **Firebase mode:** CRUD operations go to Firestore collections (`vehicles`, `expenses`), file uploads go to Cloud Storage under `comprovantes/`
- **LocalStorage fallback:** When Firebase is not configured or fails, data persists in `fleet_vehicles` and `fleet_expenses` localStorage keys

State is held in two in-memory arrays (`vehicles`, `expenses`) that are loaded on init and re-rendered entirely on every mutation via `renderAll()`.

### Firestore Collections

- **`vehicles`** — fields: `name`, `plate`, `year`, `initialKm`, `obs`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`
- **`expenses`** — fields: `vehicleId`, `type`, `date`, `value`, `km`, `obs`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, plus dynamic fields depending on expense type (fuel fields, maintenance fields, or custom fields)

### Expense Types

Type-specific form fields toggle visibility via `onExpenseTypeChange()`:
- Fuel types (`abastecimento`, `abastecimento_oleo`): show liters, price/liter, fuel type
- Maintenance types (`manutencao`, `revisao`, `troca_oleo_filtro`, `oleo`, `balde_oleo`): show description, provider
- Custom type (`outro`): show custom name, provider, and dynamic key-value field rows

### Analytics Page

The "Análises" page provides per-vehicle analytics with a shared vehicle filter:
- **Controle de Quilometragem:** tracks KM progression per vehicle (initialKm vs highest recorded km from expenses)
- **Média de Consumo (km/L):** calculates fuel efficiency using consecutive fill-up method (km delta / liters), grouped by fuel type (gasolina, diesel, etanol, gnv)
- **Gastos por Veículo:** expense breakdown — summary view (all vehicles) or detailed breakdown by expense type (single vehicle), with percentage bars

### Key Functions

- `loadData()` — initializes app data from Firestore or LocalStorage
- `saveVehicle(e)` / `saveExpense(e)` — handle form submission for create/update
- `renderAll()` — re-renders all pages (dashboard stats, tables, dropdowns, reports, analytics)
- `renderAnalytics()` — orchestrates `renderMileageControl()`, `renderFuelAverage()`, `renderExpensesByVehicle()`
- `showPage(page)` — switches visible page
- `parseMoney()` / `formatMoney()` — handle BRL currency format (`R$ 1.234,56`)

### Formatting Conventions

- Dates: `DD/MM/YYYY` display, `YYYY-MM-DD` storage
- Currency: Brazilian Real (`R$`), comma for decimals, dots for thousands
- License plates: auto-uppercased on save
